  "body": "# Requested feature\r\n\r\nIt'd be nice if we could import popular contracts in our Solidity without needing to install them as libraries. An example of that in the wild is Hardhat's console.sol being available as `import hardhat/console.sol`.\r\n\r\n# Suggested solution\r\n\r\nWeâ€™d `include_str` the solidity for some contracts in the binary, and when parsing the solidity imports in ethers-solc, weâ€™d see if any of these are imported as ``import â€˜std/Vm.solâ€™` and inject them (cc @mattsse ). \r\n\r\nExample usage: Cheatcodes, maybe Solmate or some subset of it, ..?\r\n\r\nThatâ€™d make it very easy to run forge test Foo.sol where inside it imports popular stuff, for writing quick testing â€˜scriptsâ€™ effectively. It also saves you from having to maintain a ds-test submodule lib",
